<HEAD>SAS: Not Immediately Interested in Buying Continental</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Scandinavian <ORGANIZATION>Airline Systems</ORGANIZATION> said
<DATE>Wednesday</DATE> it has no immediate interest in buying all or part of the
<ORGANIZATION>Texas Air Corp.</ORGANIZATION>'s subsidiary <ORGANIZATION>Continental Airlines</ORGANIZATION>.
   SAS Managing Director <PERSON>Jan Carlzon</PERSON> released the statement as an
answer to ``recent speculation around <ORGANIZATION>SAS</ORGANIZATION> and its cooperation
partner <ORGANIZATION>Continental Airlines</ORGANIZATION>.''
   The Wall Street Journal reported last month that <ORGANIZATION>SAS</ORGANIZATION> was involved
in advanced talks with <ORGANIZATION>Texas Air</ORGANIZATION>, which had said it may consider
selling a minority or controlling interest in <ORGANIZATION>Continental</ORGANIZATION>.
   The governments of <LOCATION>Sweden</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Denmark</LOCATION> and <LOCATION>Norway</LOCATION> own half of <ORGANIZATION>SAS</ORGANIZATION>,
and the other half is in private or corporate hands.
   ``The cooperation between <ORGANIZATION>SAS</ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION>Cointinental</ORGANIZATION> is already a great
success and has given <ORGANIZATION>SAS</ORGANIZATION> an excellent vantage point to service the
American market,'' <PERSON>Carlzon</PERSON> said.
   ``If <ORGANIZATION>Texas Air</ORGANIZATION> decided to sell <ORGANIZATION>Continental</ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION>SAS</ORGANIZATION> of course would
guard its interests,'' he said, adding that <ORGANIZATION>SAS</ORGANIZATION> was ``so pleased
with the current cooperation that the issue of buying <ORGANIZATION>Continental</ORGANIZATION>
for the time being is not of immediate interest.''
   <ORGANIZATION>SAS</ORGANIZATION>, which has a 9.9 percent stake in <ORGANIZATION>Texas Air</ORGANIZATION>, would not be
able to buy <ORGANIZATION>Continental</ORGANIZATION> outright since foreign companies are barred
from having more than a <PERCENT>25 percent</PERCENT> share in a <LOCATION>U.S.</LOCATION> carrier.
   <ORGANIZATION>SAS</ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION>Continental</ORGANIZATION> began work in <DATE>June 1988</DATE> on a joint marketing
agreement.
</TEXT>
